snippet.textDisplay: I love how everyone is so damn attached to Jeremy Richard and May, but grow up lads it isn't bad! The old crew are done for now anyways James recently said he doesn't think he can do grand tour much longer and they have cut to ocasionall specials. This and last series top gear has got so damn good! It's back to the old stuff, cheap car challenges crazy adventures. Yes I totally agree the first 200 presenters were utter dog shite. Chris Harris brings the knowledge and brilliant brilliant car info in clever new ways like the every day car series. Flintoff is a nutter who would do stuff that the old team would never do such as the dam jump in the car and the other bloke who is a comedian brings humour and weirdly considering he doesn't know anything about cars. Brings the best cars to the challenges....its not as forced as it used to be....cars actually don't make it to the end of the adventures....they show when things really do go wrong. I get people are stuck in there ways at are nostalgic, I grew up on top gear and watched every single episode 100 times over I still do, but now we finally have some competition, like if you really really don't like it than don't watch it you have grand tour, but it's nice to have the option for a seccond opinion don't be so quick to judge....
